								<h2 class="post-excerpt"><p>Peppermint is more than just a holiday candy.  The oil can be used for multiple things that are both medicinal and edible.</p>
</h2>
								<div class="KonaBody"><p> Peppermint is typically associated with the holidays, but the oil can be used every day of the year.
 </p>
<ol>
<li> Put 5-6 drops of peppermint oil in the tub or shower before you start the water.  The scent revives you and clears your head for a long day.</li>
<li> If you get bad headaches, put a few drops of Peppermint Oil on a cold, wet washcloth and place over your eyes.  The cold and smell relaxes your senses.  Make sure the oil doesn&#8217;t get into your eyes.</li>
<li> Add a few drops of Peppermint Oil to white chocolate before you heat the chocolate.  Then dip pretzels in the hot chocolate.  A great treat!</li>
<li> One drop of peppermint oil in a cup of herbal tea helps digestion and has been known to ease heartburn</li>
<li> Buy unscented body cream and add a few drops of peppermint oil.  It becomes a wonderful cream to massage with.</li>
<li> Inhale peppermint oil at your lowest point in the day.  It will revive your energy.</li>
<li> Place a few drops of peppermint oil on an oil burner and increase the energy in the room</li>
<li> Drop a bit of peppermint oil in a footbath with rolling water to aid in relieving tired feet</li>
<li> Add 2-3 drops of peppermint oil to a dry washcloth.  Put the washcloth in the dryer with your clothes.</li>
<li> You can make your own massage oil by adding 4-5 drops of peppermint oil to every 1 oz. of skin approved vegetable oil.  </li>
</ol>

